# Inner Peak Colorado — Page Consistency

- Applies to all pages in `apps/inner-peak-colorado` across every route family (`/what-we-treat`, `/therapy`, `/levels-of-care`, `/about`, `/admissions`, `/locations`, etc.).
- Match the established aesthetic from existing pages: elegant serif-led headlines, soft neutral backgrounds, dark green section anchors, and warm accent CTAs.
- Keep section rhythm consistent: hero with breadcrumb and dual CTA, condition/topic context content blocks, treatment/approach sections, FAQ accordion, and a closing CTA split section.
- Preserve spacing cadence and card language already used across the site (rounded asymmetrical corners `rounded-[2rem_0.75rem_2rem_0.75rem]` / `rounded-[0.75rem_2rem_0.75rem_2rem]`, subtle gradients, calm transitions, readable line-height).
- Color palette: `bg-[#FAF8F5]` (primary cream), `bg-[#F0ECE1]` (warm cream), `bg-[#2C3B2E]` (dark forest green), accent `#8FA489`, warm `#C8795A`, gold `#DDA15E`.
- Keep visual tone clinically credible and emotionally warm; avoid introducing radically different layout systems, novelty interactions, or off-brand color palettes.
- Always use thin route wrappers at `src/app/**/page.tsx` (metadata + JSON-LD schema only) that render view components from `src/views/**/page.tsx`.
- Reference implementation: `apps/inner-peak-colorado/src/views/what-we-treat/ptsd-and-trauma/page.tsx` is the canonical example of a fully compliant page.
- Maintain internal-link and CTA patterns (`/contact`, `tel:+17197338556`, relevant supporting pages) unless a specific page requirement says otherwise.
- Icons: Remix Icon only (`ri-*-line` classes). No other icon libraries.
- Images: `next/image` with `fill`, sourced from `https://papiwmobmdbtzeeebmpr.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/site-assets/images/`.
